overview: "The user initiated a request to fix a pull request with numerous
  issues, including critical security vulnerabilities and functional bugs, which
  were also causing Vercel deployments to fail. The agent systematically
  addressed each code-related problem: replacing an insecure authentication
  cookie with HMAC-signed sessions using Web Crypto API for Edge Runtime
  compatibility, implementing pagination bounds for API routes and CSV exports,
  correcting PDF metric calculations, enhancing number field flexibility, wiring
  up UI elements, and adding robust time input validation. A significant portion
  of the conversation involved debugging persistent Vercel deployment failures.
  This led to fixing a missing database URL in the Prisma schema, upgrading
  Next.js to resolve a critical security vulnerability (which in turn
  necessitated adapting to Prisma 7 breaking changes and updating ESLint
  configurations), and finally, lazy-loading the Prisma client to prevent
  build-time connection errors. The ultimate conclusion for the remaining Vercel
  deployment failures was a lack of configured environment variables on the
  Vercel platform itself."
